COVID-19 Status

As of 4:19PM PT yesterday, over 1.4 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.5 thousand have died.

In the last day, 336 new infections were reported and 4 deaths. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 46 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 79.8% have their 1st shot and 58.3% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 9.2 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~22 days for new deliveries to get into arms. At the current rate, all Canadians aged 12+ will have the first dose by Dec-10 and fully vaccinated by 2022-Jan-07. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
